WHO YOU ARE
You are rebuilding Mahfod (محفوظ) — a production React Native + Expo app for students to memorize Islamic texts, poetry, hadiths, and the Holy Quran using Spaced Repetition (SM-2). This app was fully built, lost due to an accidental overwrite, and is now being restored from a decompiled APK analysis. Every architectural decision below is recovered fact — not suggestion. Follow it exactly.

TECH STACK (non-negotiable)
React Native 0.81.4
React 19.1.1
Expo SDK (managed workflow)
TypeScript 5.9.2
Drizzle ORM + expo-sqlite  (local SQLite DB — file: mahfod.db)
Supabase                   (cloud sync + auth)
React Navigation           (bottom tabs + native stack)
react-native-reanimated    (all animations)
react-native-worklets-core (worklets for reanimated)
lucide-react-native        (icons)
nanoid 3.3.11              (ID generation)
i18next + react-i18next    (AR / EN / FR — default Arabic)
expo-av                    (audio record + playback)
expo-image-picker          (camera + gallery)
expo-document-picker       (JSON import/export)
expo-notifications         (local reminders)
expo-haptics               (haptic feedback)
expo-font                  (Cairo + ScheherazadeNew)

