KEY FEATURE SPECS
Memo Card (MemoListScreen)

Two view modes: Face (cover cards, full art) and Spine (bookshelf row view)
Shows: title, label badge, stage badge, relative date (now / X hours ago / yesterday / X days ago)
Long press → options: Edit, Delete, Open & Save
Chain parts shown as Part 1 / Part 2 / ...
Favorites section at top

Poetry Mode (AddMemoScreen)

Toggle splits text field into two inputs side by side:

Sadr (صدر) — first hemistich
Ajz (عجز) — second hemistich


Both stored together in text field as JSON: {"sadr":"...","ajz":"..."}

Audio Recording

Per-memo and per-verse (Lessons)
Uses expo-av — record to temp file, save URI to DB
Playback with waveform progress bar

Chain Linking

A memo can be linked to a parent memo via related_memo_id
Creates a chain: Part 1 → Part 2 → Part 3 ...
AddMemoScreen has a search-and-link UI

AI Quiz Generation

Sends memo text to an AI endpoint
Config: agent (fast/analytical), difficulty, subject/discipline, question count
Returns Q&A flashcard pairs stored as tags JSON on the memo

Quran Module — Tatbeet

Organized: Juz → Hizb → Thumn (⅛ of a Hizb)
Tatbeet session: user recites, taps error counter for each mistake
Session summary shown after completion
Supported reciters: المنشاوي، الحصري، العفاسي، الشاطري، أبو بكر الشاطري، أحمد العجمي، عبدالله بسفر، عبدالرحمن السديس

Sharing (SharingScreen) — 3 tabs

Browse (تصفح) — public matns searchable
Mine (متوني) — my shared matns, toggle public/private
Received (مُرسَلة) — matns sent to me directly

Export / Import

Export: full app data as JSON file (via expo-document-picker)
Import: merge JSON backup into local DB
Export PDF for study notes (light/dark theme)


CODING RULES

TypeScript strict mode — no any, always type everything
RTL-first — use I18nManager.isRTL, test all layouts in Arabic
Offline-first — all reads from SQLite, writes go to SQLite first then sync queue
Never hardcode strings — always use i18n keys
Use nanoid for all ID generation: import { nanoid } from 'nanoid/non-secure'
Drizzle queries only — no raw SQL strings except migrations
Reanimated for ALL animations — no Animated API from RN core
Colors from theme only — never hardcode hex values inline
Cairo font for all UI — ScheherazadeNew for Quran/hadith body text
Commit to GitHub after every working screen — this is mandatory


BUILD ORDER (implement in this exact order)
Phase 1 — Foundation
  [ ] DB schema + Drizzle client
  [ ] i18n setup (ar/en/fr)
  [ ] Theme + fonts
  [ ] Navigation shell (tabs + stacks)
  [ ] SM-2 logic (sm2.ts)

Phase 2 — Core Loop
  [ ] AddMemoScreen (new memo)
  [ ] MemoListScreen (browse)
  [ ] ReviewScreen (daily review)
  [ ] HomeScreen (dashboard)

Phase 3 — Rich Features
  [ ] TestScreen
  [ ] AddMemoScreen: poetry mode, audio, image, chain linking
  [ ] SettingsScreen (all settings)
  [ ] Vanish modes

Phase 4 — Content Modules
  [ ] LessonsScreen + MatnDetail
  [ ] StudyNotesScreen + PDF export
  [ ] QuranScreen / TatbeetTab

Phase 5 — Social + Sync
  [ ] LoginScreen + Supabase auth
  [ ] SharingScreen (3 tabs)
  [ ] Cloud sync queue
  [ ] OnboardingScreen (4 slides)

Phase 6 — Polish
  [ ] StatsScreen
  [ ] AboutScreen
  [ ] Push notifications
  [ ] AI Quiz integration

